---
const pillars = [
  {
    n: '01',
    title: 'Then',
    sub: 'Opera houses, festival stages, the Chaos Computer Club. Code that had to work the moment the lights went down.',
  },
  {
    n: '02',
    title: 'Now',
    sub: 'CTO at early-stage companies where technology is the product. Architecture decisions, engineering culture, AI integration — and the hundred daily calls that determine whether a team ships or stalls.',
  },
  {
    n: '03',
    title: 'Always',
    sub: 'A deep instinct for where technology and human experience meet — and a low tolerance for systems that ignore either one.',
  },
];
---

<section id="what-i-do" class="wid-section">

  <div class="wid-layout">

    <!-- Left: hero intro -->
    <div class="wid-intro">
      <div class="wid-header">
        <span class="section-label">— The Short Version</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-eyebrow fade-in" data-delay="100">
        <span>CTO</span>
        <span>Creative Technologist</span>
        <span>AI · Real-Time Systems</span>
        <span>Berlin</span>
      </div>
      <p class="hero-body fade-up" data-delay="200">
        I started on stages. Now I run engineering at startups. The through-line is the same: making complex systems work under pressure, with no room to fake it.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Right: pillars -->
    <div class="wid-right">
      <div class="wid-lead fade-up" data-delay="0">
        <p>
          I spent the first half of my career writing software that ran live — real-time visuals synchronised to an opera score, signal processing tools for touring electronic musicians, video systems for theater productions where the curtain goes up whether your code is ready or not.
        </p>
        <p class="wid-lead-p2">
          For the past six years I've been a CTO and technical co-founder at venture-backed startups — building adaptive music engines with machine learning at their core, porting robotics vision systems from prototype to production, leading teams through product launches and the quiet chaos that follows. <strong>I was training models on performance data and shipping generative systems before the current AI wave</strong> — which means I understand the technology from the inside, not from a pitch deck.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="wid-grid">
        {pillars.map((p, i) => (
          <div class="pillar fade-up" data-delay={String(i * 90)}>
            <span class="pillar-num">{p.n}</span>
            <h3 class="pillar-title">{p.title}</h3>
            <p class="pillar-sub">{p.sub}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

</section>

<style>
  .wid-section {
    background: #F0EDE6;
    padding: 6rem 3.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #D4CFC6;
  }

  /* Two-column layout */
  .wid-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr;
    gap: 5rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  /* Left column */
  .wid-intro {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    position: sticky;
    top: 6rem;
  }

  .wid-header {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .section-label {
    font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #9A9288;
  }

  .hero-eyebrow {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.35rem;
  }
  .hero-eyebrow span {
    font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #D4CFC6;
    background: #0E0D0B;
    padding: 0.3em 0.65em;
  }

  .hero-body {
    font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: #6B6456;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }

  /* Right column */
  .wid-right {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .wid-lead {
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .wid-lead p {
    font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: clamp(0.95rem, 1.5vw, 1.1rem);
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: #6B6456;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }

  .wid-lead-p2 {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }

  .wid-lead strong {
    font-weight: 500;
    color: #0E0D0B;
  }

  /* ── Grid: brutalist horizontal rule dividers ── */
  .wid-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    border-top: 2px solid #0E0D0B;
  }

  .pillar {
    padding: 2.5rem 2.5rem 2.5rem 0;
    border-right: 1px solid #D4CFC6;
  }
  .pillar:last-child { border-right: none; padding-right: 0; }
  .pillar:not(:first-child) { padding-left: 2.5rem; }

  .pillar-num {
    font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    color: #C4BFB6;
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 1.4rem;
  }

  .pillar-title {
    font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 2.2vw, 1.75rem);
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    line-height: 1.1;
    color: #0E0D0B;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
    white-space: pre-line;
  }

  .pillar-sub {
    font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: #9A9288;
    white-space: pre-line;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .wid-layout {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 3rem;
    }
    .wid-intro { position: static; }
    .hero-eyebrow { flex-direction: row; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  }

  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .wid-section { padding: 4rem 1.75rem; }
    .wid-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      border-top: 2px solid #0E0D0B;
    }
    .pillar {
      border-right: none;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #D4CFC6;
      padding: 2rem 0;
    }
    .pillar:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
    .pillar:not(:first-child) { padding-left: 0; }
  }
</style>
